<h2 id="specifications" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#specifications"><span>Specifications</span></a></h2>
<p>The cookbook also contains the Stone specifications, which delve into the abstract concepts behind the framework and the implementation details of each module. This documentation is not only crucial for using Stone.js but can also be utilized to create a Stone framework or application in any other programming languages. Stone.js is not merely a JavaScript framework; it represents a next-generation micro framework that uses the Continuum Architecture to create Omniplex applications.</p>
<p>Omniplex applications emphasize the omnipresence of the modern applications, meaning they can run anywhere, locally, on servers, in the cloud, as cloud functions (FaaS), and beyond without changing core functionalities or configurations. This makes the application adaptable and scalable across different platforms, pushing the boundaries of modern web development.</p>
